# DocuRAG — Document Question Answering System

Upload any PDF or text document and ask questions about it in plain English. DocuRAG finds the most relevant parts of your document and generates a grounded answer — the answer always comes from your document, not from the model guessing.

---

## How it works

**Chunking** — The document is split into overlapping 300-word chunks so no information is lost at boundaries.

**Embedding** — Each chunk is converted into a 384-dimensional vector using `all-MiniLM-L6-v2` (Sentence Transformers). Chunks that mean similar things end up mathematically close to each other.

**Retrieval** — When you ask a question, it is also converted into a vector. FAISS searches the index and returns the top 5 most relevant chunks using cosine similarity — this is semantic search, not keyword matching.

**Generation** — The retrieved chunks are passed as context to `google/flan-t5-base`. The model reads only those chunks and generates a concise answer. If the answer is not in the document, it says so.

```
Document → Chunker → Embeddings → FAISS Index
                                       ↑
                               Question Vector
                                       ↓
                           Top-5 Chunks → Flan-T5 → Answer
```

